Does anyone ever experienced with this error `1535-2103/system_process E/WindowManager: Unable to transfer touch focus`
What i tried to do is trigger/delegate `LongClick` event from `PopupWindow` to underlying view to `startDrag()`

code in underlying view
```
@Override
    public boolean onLongClick(View v) {
        if (!isDragAllowed()) {
            return false;
        }

        startDrag(v);

        dragAllowed = false;

        return false;
    }
```

But above error always shown when `startDrag()` get called and `startDrag()` itself always return false

I know that inside `startDrag()` method that is a process `performDrag()` that cause the result was false

the value for them is set up with ```    public static final int REQUEST_CODE_BIO_IMAGE_TAKE_PICTURE = ActivityUtils.generateRequestCode();
    public static final int REQUEST_CODE_BIO_IMAGE_SELECT_IMAGE = ActivityUtils.generateRequestCode();
    public static final int REQUEST_CODE_BIO_IMAGE_DELETE_IMAGE = ActivityUtils.generateRequestCode();
    public static final int REQUEST_CODE_BANNER_IMAGE_TAKE_PICTURE = ActivityUtils.generateRequestCode();
    public static final int REQUEST_CODE_BANNER_IMAGE_SELECT_IMAGE = ActivityUtils.generateRequestCode();
    public static final int REQUEST_CODE_BANNER_IMAGE_DELETE_IMAGE = ActivityUtils.generateRequestCode();```  Where `ActivityUtils.generateRequestCode()` is a static method that just increments an `AtomicInteger` and returns the value

```
public enum MyRequestCodes {    
    REQUEST_CODE_BIO_IMAGE_TAKE_PICTURE(ActivityUtils.generateRequestCode()),
    REQUEST_CODE_BIO_IMAGE_SELECT_IMAGE(ActivityUtils.generateRequestCode()),
    REQUEST_CODE_BIO_IMAGE_DELETE_IMAGE(ActivityUtils.generateRequestCode()),
    REQUEST_CODE_BANNER_IMAGE_TAKE_PICTURE(ActivityUtils.generateRequestCode()),
    REQUEST_CODE_BANNER_IMAGE_SELECT_IMAGE(ActivityUtils.generateRequestCode()),
    REQUEST_CODE_BANNER_IMAGE_DELETE_IMAGE(ActivityUtils.generateRequestCode());

    private final int requestCode;

    MyRequestCodes(int requestCode){
    	this.requestCode = requestCode;
    }

    public int requestCode(){
    	return requestCode;
    }
}
```

